---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const title = "BRIK Market Update — Days on Market (DOM)";
const description = "The advantage just flipped. Buyers hold the cards.";
---
<BaseLayout title={`${title} | BRIK`} description={description}>
  <section style="padding:28px 0 10px">
    <h2 style="font-size:30px;margin:0 0 10px;letter-spacing:-.4px">{title}</h2>
    <p style="margin:0 0 18px;color:var(--muted);max-width:82ch">{description}</p>

    <div class="card">
      <h3 style="margin:0 0 8px">🧠 Term of the Week: "Days on Market (DOM)"</h3>
      <p style="margin:0 0 10px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        <strong style="color:var(--text)">What it means:</strong> How long a home is listed before going under contract.
      </p>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 12px;padding-left:18px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        <li>"Days on Market" just means how many days a home has been sitting for sale.</li>
        <li>The longer it's listed, the more flexible the seller usually becomes.</li>
        <li>It's a key signal for when you, the buyer, can make a move on your terms.</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin:0;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        <strong style="color:var(--text)">🧱 BRIK Block:</strong> Think of it like shoes sitting on a store shelf. If they're still there after a couple weeks, you're probably catching a discount. Homes are the same right now — more time = more leverage.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="margin-top:14px">
      <h3 style="margin:0 0 8px">📈 Georgia & Atlanta Market Snapshot</h3>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 12px;padding-left:18px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        <li>Georgia Median Home Value: $329,110 (+0.3% YoY)</li>
        <li>Atlanta Median Sales Price: $407,000 (flat YoY)</li>
        <li>Median Days on Market: Georgia – 50 days | Atlanta – 47 days</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin:0 0 10px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        Homes are taking longer to sell compared to 2023, giving buyers more time, flexibility, and negotiating power.
      </p>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 12px;padding-left:18px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        <li>More DOM means buyers don't have to rush.</li>
        <li>Sellers are more open to negotiations, credits, or repairs.</li>
        <li>You get time to think, compare, and make smarter decisions.</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin:0;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        <strong style="color:var(--text)">🧱 BRIK Block:</strong> Think of it like bidding solo at a car auction. You have more say in the outcome. You walk away with better terms.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="margin-top:14px">
      <h3 style="margin:0 0 8px">💼 Financing Spotlight: Conventional ARMs</h3>
      <p style="margin:0 0 10px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        An Adjustable-Rate Mortgage (ARM) is a loan with a lower fixed interest rate for the first several years — currently 7 — before adjusting annually. ARMs are pricing about <strong style="color:var(--text)">0.5% lower</strong> than 30-year fixed loans.
      </p>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 12px;padding-left:18px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        <li>You get a lower payment for the first 7 years.</li>
        <li>After that, the rate adjusts with the market.</li>
        <li>Most people refinance or move before it ever changes.</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin:0;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        <strong style="color:var(--text)">🧱 BRIK Block:</strong> It's like getting a rent discount locked in for 7 years. You can renegotiate (refinance) before the rate changes. A smart strategy if you're not staying long-term.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="margin-top:14px">
      <h3 style="margin:0 0 8px">🔨 Renovation Loans: Unlock More Inventory</h3>
      <p style="margin:0 0 10px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        Renovation loans allow you to finance both the purchase and the upgrades, giving you access to homes that may need work but offer real value.
      </p>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 12px;padding-left:18px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        <li><strong style="color:var(--text)">Fannie Mae Homestyle:</strong> 97% financing, fixed rate</li>
        <li><strong style="color:var(--text)">FHA 203(k):</strong> Lower credit score acceptance, more oversight</li>
        <li><strong style="color:var(--text)">Construction-Perm:</strong> Full creative control, higher down payment</li>
        <li><strong style="color:var(--text)">Invest Atlanta Renovation Advantage Loan:</strong> Down payment and renovation assistance for eligible City of Atlanta buyers</li>
        <li>Pair this with conventional loans and get support on both the home and the fix-up budget</li>
      </ul>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 12px;padding-left:18px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        <li>You can buy the house and finance the renovations — all in one mortgage.</li>
        <li>This opens up homes others overlook.</li>
        <li>It's your chance to design the future version of your home.</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin:0;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        <strong style="color:var(--text)">🧱 BRIK Block:</strong> It's like buying a used car and rolling the upgrades into the loan. You're not just buying what it looks like now — you're buying what it can become. This gives you more options in a competitive market.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="margin-top:14px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.03)">
      <h3 style="margin:0 0 8px">Final Word from BRIK</h3>
      <p style="margin:0 0 10px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">We're in a rare window:</p>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 12px;padding-left:18px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        <li>✔️ Homes are sitting longer</li>
        <li>✔️ Sellers are more flexible</li>
        <li>✔️ Financing is becoming more strategic</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin:0;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7">
        If you've been waiting for a sign — this is it. Let's talk strategy and find your next move — BRIK BY BRIK.
      </p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:12px">
        <a class="pill" href="/newsletter">Back to Newsletter</a>
        <a class="pill primary" href="/intake">Submit Intake</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
